items.title: Bus and truck collision kills 37 in Brazil
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
A crash between a passenger bus and a truck early Saturday killed 37 people on a highway in Minas Gerais, a state in southeastern Brazil, officials said. The Minas Gerais fire department, which responded to the scene, said 13 others were taken to hospitals near the city of Teofilo Otoni. The bus had reportedly departed from Sao Paulo and was carrying 45 passengers.

items.title: Samosa delight - how a grandmother’s festive food twist is creating Christmas cheer
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
A beloved grandmother’s passion for making samosas has grown into a thriving family business, spreading warmth and tradition far beyond her community. What started as a family tradition is now a slick business operation offering hand-made samosas to homes across the UK and beyond - now with a festive-themed twist.

items.title: 12 children among 19 people killed by Israeli airstrikes in Gaza
items.author: Associated Press
items.content:
Mourners in the Gaza Strip held funerals on Saturday for 19 people, including 12 children, who were killed in separate Israeli strikes on Friday and overnight. One strike on Friday afternoon hit a residential building in the built-up Nuseirat refugee camp in central Gaza, killing at least seven Palestinians, including five children and one woman, and injuring 16 others, health officials said. (Production by Wafaa Shurafa)
